{"id":13483,"date":"2023-02-16T22:42:13","date_gmt":"2023-02-16T22:42:13","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/?page_id=13483"},"modified":"2023-10-05T03:55:21","modified_gmt":"2023-10-05T03:55:21","slug":"benefits-of-aba-therapy","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/benefits-of-aba-therapy\/","title":{"rendered":"Benefits of ABA Therapy"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;20&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357588359{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357006855{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-family: Antonio; font-size: 40px; color: #333333;\"><strong>The Benefits of ABA Therapy<\/strong><\/span>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676936849460{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">Children and young adults with\u00a0<span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><a style=\"color: #f27822;\" href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/autism-spectrum-disorder\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD)<\/strong><\/a><\/span>\u00a0and other related developmental disorders face unique challenges daily with the specificity and intensity varying from individual to individual. Challenges often include speech, language, and communication which means that some may find it difficult to have a conversation, some may only speak a handful of words, and others may be completely nonverbal.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">Employing a holistic and individualized approach, ABA specialists ensure that the behavior treatment plan addresses the needs of the child or young adult as well as with the family and home dynamics.\u00a0\u00a0Treatment goals are established by age and functional ability. Goals can include specific behaviors or many different skill areas.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner gap=&#8221;15&#8243;][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rotateIn&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14596 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Smell-Icon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"192\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Smell-Icon.png 449w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Smell-Icon-296x300.png 296w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676936859096{padding-right: 25px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">Developmental disorders can often include\u00a0<span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><strong>a heightened sense of smell or touch<\/strong>\u00a0<\/span>which makes elements of self-care an uncomfortable experience.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">ABA therapy helps to manage discomfort while increasing the overall level of functioning including self-help and daily living skills such as toileting, self-feeding, and morning and afternoon routines.\u00a0<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rotateIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693287218944{padding-right: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14591 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"192\" height=\"192\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741.png 600w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741-500x500.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_4201741-384x384.png 384w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676646866876{padding-right: 25px !important;padding-left: 25px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\"><span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><strong>Negative\/maladaptive behaviors<\/strong><\/span>\u00a0hinder functioning at an appropriate level.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">ABA therapy utilizes one-on-one interaction to establish an effective foundation in reducing the frequency of self-stimulatory, aggressive and self-injurious behaviors.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rotateIn&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-13569\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Communication-icon-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"192\" height=\"192\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Communication-icon-1.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Communication-icon-1-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Communication-icon-1-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/02\/Communication-icon-1-120x120.png 120w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676646875866{padding-right: 25px !important;padding-left: 25px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">Functional communication is defined as the ability to effectively communicate needs and wants. Those with\u00a0<span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><strong>significant language impairments<\/strong>\u00a0<\/span>can be taught to use a functional language system to reduce frustration and anxiety.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">ABA therapy can teach how to appropriately identify and name items and\/or people, ask for what may be needed and develop the ability to engage in dialogue.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner gap=&#8221;15&#8243;][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rotateIn&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14593 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"192\" height=\"193\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n.png 518w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n-298x300.png 298w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n-500x503.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Friends-icon-n-384x384.png 384w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676936932276{padding-right: 25px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">Social skills are foundational elements for social interactions and peer relationships. Development disorders can cause\u00a0<span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><strong>delays in learning social skills<\/strong><\/span>\u00a0including play, conversation and problem-solving abilities.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">ABA therapy helps to learn how to behave in different social situations as well as in family dynamics.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rotateIn&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693287295939{padding-right: 20px !important;}&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-14587\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"192\" height=\"192\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810.png 3278w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-1024x1024.png 1024w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-150x150.png 150w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-768x768.png 768w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-1536x1536.png 1536w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-2048x2048.png 2048w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-500x500.png 500w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-800x800.png 800w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-1280x1280.png 1280w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-1920x1920.png 1920w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-100x100.png 100w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-120x120.png 120w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/PngItem_797810-384x384.png 384w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676646943673{padding-right: 25px !important;padding-left: 25px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">Picky eaters hamper recommended nutrients needed to thrive. Research shows that\u00a0<span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><strong>food selectivity often fails to resolve itself without intervention<\/strong>.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">ABA therapy addresses food-related problems.\u00a0Further, the sooner intervention can occur, the more likely good eating habits can be established.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=&#8221;1\/3&#8243;][vc_column_text css_animation=&#8221;rotateIn&#8221;]<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-image-14594 aligncenter\" src=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Picture41.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"192\" height=\"196\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Picture41.png 447w, https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/08\/Picture41-294x300.png 294w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 192px) 100vw, 192px\" \/>[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676646952538{padding-right: 25px !important;padding-left: 25px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\"><span style=\"color: #f27822;\"><strong>Cognitive development<\/strong><\/span>\u00a0focuses on how information is processed including language.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; color: #3a3b3c;\">ABA therapy strengthens cognitive development\u00a0such as letter and word recognition, reading, writing and gross and fine motor skills.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_column_inner][\/vc_row_inner][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357516755{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;13516&#8243; img_size=&#8221;large&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_3d&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676594205991{padding-left: 100px !important;}&#8221;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693707851043{margin-left: -40px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"font-size: 18px; color: #333333; font-family: 'Archivo Black';\"><strong>Personalized ABA therapy<\/strong>\u00a0<strong>almost always begins with intensive one-on-one sessions that create areas of focus for therapy goals.\u00a0 <\/strong><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Behavior assessments are used to determine behavior and to understand the reasons behind such behavior. <strong>Functional Behavior Assessment (FBA)\u00a0<\/strong>is used to determine the behavior of a child or young adult and to understand the reasons behind such behavior.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Each behavior serves a purpose whether your child or young adult realizes it or not. This assessment allows us to observe the child or young adult at home and determine the elements and origins of certain behaviors which then helps us understand the root cause of a behavior in order to change it.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040; font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed';\">With a comprehensive assessment, the information gathered is integral in developing a treatment protocol that helps to develop skills that promote independence and growth.\u00a0<\/span>[\/vc_column_text]\t<div class=\"evc-button-wrapper evc-btn-left\">\n<a class=\"evc-button evc-shortcode  evc-btn-solid evc-btn-large \" href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/what-is-aba-therapy\/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-family: mulish;font-size: 16px;color: #ffffff;background-color: #00b3e6;margin: 0px 90px 0px 0px\" data-hover-color=\"#ffffff\" data-hover-background-color=\"#f3781e\">\n\t\t<span class=\"evc-btn-text\">MORE ABOUT ABA THERAPY<\/span>\n<\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n[\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693288559505{padding-top: 50px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357386864{margin-left: 100px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #3a3b3c;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Barlow Semi Condensed'; font-size: 18pt;\"><b><span style=\"font-family: 'Archivo Black'; font-size: 18px;\">Challenging behavior can be improved when we understand the root causes behind displayed behavior.<\/span><br \/>\n<\/b><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Some children have trouble communicating their emotions and their needs. The\u00a0<i>level<\/i>\u00a0of difficulty varies from child to child; however, for many, limited communication skills are likely a way of expression that may include physically-exhibiting behaviors such as tantrums.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Through ABA and its treatment protocol, children may learn several essential life skills such as following instructions, language and communication, motor skills, and self-help, all skills that are integral to the classroom environment and in later years.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Continual progress depends on objective data that provides a definitive view of the progress made and the areas where the protocol is insufficient.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text]\t<div class=\"evc-button-wrapper evc-btn-left\">\n<a class=\"evc-button evc-shortcode  evc-btn-solid evc-btn-large \" href=\"https:\/\/www.kidzcompanion.com\/aba-therapy-behavior\/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"font-family: mulish;font-size: 16px;color: #ffffff;background-color: #00b3e6;margin: 0px 0px 0px 90px\" data-hover-color=\"#ffffff\" data-hover-background-color=\"#f3781e\">\n\t\t<span class=\"evc-btn-text\">MORE ABOUT ABA &amp; BEHAVIOR<\/span>\n<\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n[\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;13517&#8243; img_size=&#8221;large&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_3d&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676593739690{padding-left: 100px !important;}&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row][vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676594451334{padding-top: 50px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_single_image image=&#8221;13518&#8243; img_size=&#8221;large&#8221; style=&#8221;vc_box_shadow_3d&#8221; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676594336539{padding-left: 100px !important;}&#8221;][\/vc_column][vc_column width=&#8221;1\/2&#8243;][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357430315{margin-left: -40px !important;}&#8221;]<span style=\"color: #3a3b3c;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Archivo Black'; font-size: 18pt; color: #333333;\"><strong>Parents &amp; family<\/strong><\/span><span style=\"font-family: Alegreya; font-size: 20pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Archivo Black'; font-size: 18pt; color: #333333;\"><strong> are <\/strong><\/span><b><span style=\"font-family: 'Archivo Black'; color: #333333;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">valued part of the team<\/span><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">.<\/span><\/span><br \/>\n<\/b><\/span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">Parents play a critical role in the development of a treatment plan as no one knows the child or young adult better. Taking an active role greatly optimizes the benefits of therapy.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\">ABA therapy is an approach that is not only inclusive for a child or young adult but also for parents\/guardians and families. Parents and families often feel alone and at odds, somehow separated from the process designed for their child or young adult.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 16px; color: #404040;\"><strong>Parents and immediate family<\/strong> are essential to all treatment protocols. After all, they are the first teacher a child has. Our goal is to educate and help the parent to better support their child outside of the classroom setting.<\/span>[\/vc_column_text]\t<div class=\"evc-button-wrapper evc-btn-left\">\n<a class=\"evc-button evc-shortcode  evc-btn-solid evc-btn-large \"  style=\"font-family: mulish;font-size: 16px;color: #ffffff;background-color: #00b3e6\" data-hover-color=\"#ffffff\" data-hover-background-color=\"#f3781e\">\n\t\t<span class=\"evc-btn-text\">MORE ABOUT PARENT\/FAMILY COACHING<\/span>\n<\/a>\n\t<\/div>\n[vc_empty_space height=&#8221;64px&#8221;][\/vc_column][\/vc_row]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row full_width=&#8221;stretch_row_content&#8221; gap=&#8221;20&#8243; css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357588359{padding-top: 40px !important;padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;][vc_column][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1693357006855{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]The Benefits of ABA Therapy[\/vc_column_text][vc_column_text css=&#8221;.vc_custom_1676936849460{padding-right: 80px !important;padding-left: 80px !important;}&#8221;]Children and young adults with\u00a0Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD)\u00a0and other related developmental disorders face unique challenges daily with the specificity and intensity varying from individual to individual. Challenges often include speech, language, and [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"redux-templates_contained